<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>
  Prep research for decision
  <a href="/backlog/974-define-the-maas-wrapper-serve-protocol-cem-framework-wrapper/">#974</a>
  (blocks the live-test sandbox
  <a href="/backlog/912-polyglot-panel-live-test-sandbox-execute-the-generated-wrapp/">#912</a>; Block
  Explorer epic <a href="/backlog/746-block-explorer/">#746</a>, <code>locus: frontierui</code>).
  #974 was filed to <em>"define the MaaS wrapper-serve protocol — the CEM→framework-wrapper ESM serve
  contract a browser sandbox consumes,"</em> on the premise that <em>that protocol is not yet defined.</em>
  This research tests that premise first.
</p>

<h2>The headline finding</h2>
<p>
  The premise is false in the same way <a href="/backlog/792-component-compile-time-path/">#792</a> caught
  for the binding layer: the contract <strong>already exists</strong>. The MaaS serve-path IR
  (<code>blocks/renderers/module-service/servePathIR.ts</code>, ratified in
  <a href="/backlog/505-maas-polyglot-sot-neutral-contract-serve-path-ir-as-the-auth/">#505</a> /
  <a href="/backlog/463-polyglot-maas-origin-generate-net-java-other-server-implemen/">#463</a>) is a
  language-neutral, zero-import source of truth that already defines the URL grammar
  (<code>&lt;name&gt;[@&lt;pin&gt;].js</code>), the <code>form</code>/<code>target</code>/<code>strategy</code>
  params, content-hash identity, immutable/floating cache, ETag/SRI headers, and the 400/404/500 error
  set. A React <em>"functional component + element wrapper"</em> form already ships
  (<code>moduleService.ts</code> <code>ServeForm</code>). So #974 does <strong>not</strong> mint a new
  protocol — it reconciles the wrapper-serve need against the existing one.
</p>

