<h2>Forced invariants (supported by default)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Conform to the existing IR; do not mint a parallel protocol.</strong> Minting a second
    MaaS-shaped contract would duplicate the #505 SoT and serve drift between two contracts.</li>
  <li><strong>Identity folds the producer version.</strong> <code>protocols.json#maas-versioning</code>
    makes the version id a content hash over <em>every</em> byte-determining input — definition +
    transform/compiler version + params + provenance — and names omission <em>"the one excluded (broken)
    option."</em> So the wrapper id folds the <strong>genWrapper producer version</strong>, not CEM-hash
    only.</li>
  <li><strong>Cache + errors</strong> reuse <code>CACHE_POLICY</code> and the existing response set.</li>
  <li><strong>Bare-specifier ESM</strong>, import-map/bundler resolution at the consumer (#081/#955).</li>
  <li><strong>FUI endpoint is its own runtime</strong> conforming to the WE contract (runtime never
    crosses the WE→FUI seam — #855/#817); genWrapper is injected as its transform-provider.</li>
</ul>

<h2>The one genuine fork — framework-axis representation</h2>
<p>
  How is the framework (react/vue) carried in the contract? <strong>A1</strong> — overload the
  catalog-gated <code>form</code> param (<code>react-wrapper</code>/<code>vue-wrapper</code> as injected
  FUI catalog values; zero neutral-contract change). <strong>A2</strong> — add a distinct neutral
  <code>framework</code> param, because framework is orthogonal to <em>form</em> (wrapper vs full-rewrite
  vs wc-class) and to the ES <em>target</em>; encoding it in <code>form</code> collapses two axes into one
  enum. <strong>Recommended default: A2 (~65%)</strong> on merit — distinct axes, cleaning up the
  accidentally React-only <code>functional</code> form, matching WE's separate-and-expose bias. Residual:
  A1 is coherent and cheaper, the IR deliberately keeps value-sets injected (over-engineering risk for two
  frameworks), and <code>functional</code> shows framework-in-form has worked. High-leverage —
  <strong>flag for the deciding agent's skeptic pass.</strong>
</p>

